    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why Margin Analysis Differs for GenAI Features"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Traditional SaaS gross margin analysis separates fixed infrastructure from variable COGS. GenAI features introduce a third cost category: LLM API spend, which is variable with usage but priced per token rather than per user. This makes LLM cost behave more like payment processing fees than hosting \u2014 it scales with every conversation, not just with the number of deployed servers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Margin waterfall diagram"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Gross margin for a GenAI feature is typically 40\u201365%, compared to 70\u201380% for traditional SaaS. The LLM API cost is the primary driver of this compression. Targeting 50%+ gross margin requires keeping LLM spend below 30% of revenue."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Revenue and Cost Data Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Margin analysis requires attributing both revenue and cost to individual features. Revenue attribution depends on the pricing model (subscription seat, usage-based, or bundled). Cost attribution relies on the conversation-level tagging established in the FinOps pipeline."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass FeatureRevenueRecord:\n    \"\"\"Revenue directly attributable to one GenAI feature for one period.\"\"\"\n    feature: str\n    period: str                    # YYYY-MM\n    active_users: int\n    mrr_usd: float                 # monthly recurring revenue from this feature\n    usage_revenue_usd: float = 0.0  # pay-per-use overages if applicable\n\n    @property\n    def total_revenue_usd(self) -> float:\n        return self.mrr_usd + self.usage_revenue_usd\n\n    @property\n    def revenue_per_user_usd(self) -> float:\n        if self.active_users == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return self.total_revenue_usd / self.active_users\n\n@dataclass\nclass FeatureCostRecord:\n    feature: str\n    period: str\n    active_users: int\n    llm_cost_usd: float            # token API spend\n    infra_cost_usd: float          # compute, storage, network\n    support_alloc_usd: float       # proportional share of support headcount\n    rd_alloc_usd: float = 0.0      # engineering amortisation (optional)\n\n    @property\n    def variable_cost_usd(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Costs that scale with usage \u2014 LLM API is the dominant variable.\"\"\"\"\n        return self.llm_cost_usd + self.infra_cost_usd\n\n    @property\n    def total_cost_usd(self) -> float:\n        return self.llm_cost_usd + self.infra_cost_usd + self.support_alloc_usd + self.rd_alloc_usd\n\n    @property\n    def cost_per_user_usd(self) -> float:\n        if self.active_users == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return self.total_cost_usd / self.active_users"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Computing Margin at Feature Level"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "With revenue and cost records aligned to the same feature and period, the margin report computes gross margin (revenue minus variable costs), contribution margin (revenue minus all direct costs), and the LLM cost ratio \u2014 the key GenAI efficiency signal."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass FeatureMarginReport:\n    feature: str\n    period: str\n    active_users: int\n    revenue: FeatureRevenueRecord\n    costs: FeatureCostRecord\n\n    @property\n    def gross_profit_usd(self) -> float:\n        return self.revenue.total_revenue_usd - self.costs.variable_cost_usd\n\n    @property\n    def gross_margin_pct(self) -> float:\n        rev = self.revenue.total_revenue_usd\n        if rev == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return self.gross_profit_usd / rev * 100\n\n    @property\n    def contribution_margin_usd(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Revenue minus all direct costs (including support allocation).\"\"\"\"\n        return self.revenue.total_revenue_usd - self.costs.total_cost_usd\n\n    @property\n    def contribution_margin_pct(self) -> float:\n        rev = self.revenue.total_revenue_usd\n        if rev == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return self.contribution_margin_usd / rev * 100\n\n    @property\n    def llm_cost_ratio(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"LLM spend as a fraction of revenue \u2014 the core GenAI efficiency metric.\"\"\"\"\n        rev = self.revenue.total_revenue_usd\n        if rev == 0:\n            return float(\"inf\")\n        return self.costs.llm_cost_usd / rev\n\n    @property\n    def is_margin_healthy(self) -> bool:\n        return self.gross_margin_pct >= 50.0\n\ndef build_margin_report(\n    revenue: FeatureRevenueRecord,\n    costs: FeatureCostRecord,\n) -> FeatureMarginReport:\n    assert revenue.feature == costs.feature\n    assert revenue.period == costs.period\n    return FeatureMarginReport(\n        feature=revenue.feature,\n        period=revenue.period,\n        active_users=revenue.active_users,\n        revenue=revenue,\n        costs=costs,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Break-Even Analysis"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Break-even users is the minimum active user count at which a feature covers its fixed costs. For GenAI features, fixed costs include support allocation and R&D amortisation; variable costs are dominated by LLM API spend per user."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass BreakEvenAnalysis:\n    feature: str\n    fixed_cost_usd: float          # infra + support + R&D (don't scale with users)\n    variable_cost_per_user_usd: float  # LLM cost per active user\n    revenue_per_user_usd: float\n    current_users: int\n\n    @property\n    def contribution_per_user_usd(self) -> float:\n        return self.revenue_per_user_usd - self.variable_cost_per_user_usd\n\n    @property\n    def break_even_users(self) -> float:\n        if self.contribution_per_user_usd <= 0:\n            return float(\"inf\")  # never breaks even\n        return self.fixed_cost_usd / self.contribution_per_user_usd\n\n    @property\n    def margin_of_safety_pct(self) -> float:\n        be = self.break_even_users\n        if be == float(\"inf\") or be == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        return (self.current_users - be) / self.current_users * 100\n\n    @property\n    def is_viable(self) -> bool:\n        return self.contribution_per_user_usd > 0\n\ndef compute_break_even(\n    feature: str,\n    revenue: FeatureRevenueRecord,\n    costs: FeatureCostRecord,\n) -> BreakEvenAnalysis:\n    n = revenue.active_users\n    variable_per_user = costs.variable_cost_usd / n if n else 0.0\n    fixed = costs.support_alloc_usd + costs.rd_alloc_usd\n    return BreakEvenAnalysis(\n        feature=feature,\n        fixed_cost_usd=fixed,\n        variable_cost_per_user_usd=variable_per_user,\n        revenue_per_user_usd=revenue.revenue_per_user_usd,\n        current_users=n,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "If "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "contribution_per_user_usd"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " is negative \u2014 LLM cost per user exceeds revenue per user \u2014 the feature never breaks even regardless of scale. This is the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "unit economics death spiral"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ": more users accelerates losses."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM Cost Ratio Targets by Business Model"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The acceptable LLM-to-revenue ratio varies by how the feature is monetised. Usage-based pricing can tolerate a higher ratio because LLM cost and revenue are both proportional to consumption. Subscription models have fixed revenue per user and must enforce stricter LLM cost ceilings."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Target LLM cost ratios by business model\nLLM_RATIO_TARGETS = {\n    \"saas_subscription\":  0.10,   # LLM \u2264 10% of ARR per user\n    \"usage_based\":        0.25,   # LLM \u2264 25% of usage revenue\n    \"internal_tooling\":   0.40,   # cost-centre; margin less critical\n    \"marketplace\":        0.15,   # platform takes cut; less margin headroom\n}\n\ndef assess_llm_ratio(\n    report: FeatureMarginReport,\n    model: str = \"saas_subscription\",\n) -> dict:\n    target = LLM_RATIO_TARGETS[model]\n    ratio = report.llm_cost_ratio\n    excess = ratio - target\n    return {\n        \"feature\": report.feature,\n        \"llm_cost_ratio\": round(ratio, 4),\n        \"target_ratio\": target,\n        \"within_target\": ratio <= target,\n        \"excess_ratio\": round(excess, 4) if excess > 0 else 0.0,\n        \"action\": (\n            \"OPTIMIZE\" if excess > 0.10 else\n            \"MONITOR\"  if excess > 0 else\n            \"HEALTHY\"\n        ),\n    }"
          }
        ]
      },
