      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cohort-Level Margin Breakdown"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Aggregate margin numbers mask cohort differences. Enterprise customers typically have higher revenue per seat and lower LLM cost per user (fewer open-ended queries, more structured workflows). Free trial users often invert this \u2014 high token consumption with zero revenue. Cohort analysis reveals which segments are margin-accretive."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from statistics import mean\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\n@dataclass\nclass CohortMarginRow:\n    cohort: str          # e.g. \"enterprise\" | \"smb\" | \"free_trial\"\n    users: int\n    revenue_per_user: float\n    llm_cost_per_user: float\n    infra_cost_per_user: float\n\n    @property\n    def gross_margin_pct(self) -> float:\n        rev = self.revenue_per_user\n        if rev == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        cost = self.llm_cost_per_user + self.infra_cost_per_user\n        return (rev - cost) / rev * 100\n\ndef compute_cohort_margins(\n    conversations: list,              # list of Conversation-like objects with .team/.feature\n    revenue_by_cohort: dict[str, float],  # cohort \u2192 total MRR\n    cost_records: list[FeatureCostRecord],\n) -> list[CohortMarginRow]:\n    cohort_users: dict[str, set] = defaultdict(set)\n    for c in conversations:\n        cohort_users[c.team].add(c.user_id)\n\n    cost_by_cohort: dict[str, float] = defaultdict(float)\n    for rec in cost_records:\n        cost_by_cohort[rec.feature] += rec.llm_cost_usd\n\n    rows = []\n    for cohort, user_ids in cohort_users.items():\n        n = len(user_ids)\n        rev = revenue_by_cohort.get(cohort, 0.0)\n        llm = cost_by_cohort.get(cohort, 0.0)\n        rows.append(CohortMarginRow(\n            cohort=cohort,\n            users=n,\n            revenue_per_user=rev / n if n else 0.0,\n            llm_cost_per_user=llm / n if n else 0.0,\n            infra_cost_per_user=0.50,  # flat infra alloc per user\n        ))\n    return sorted(rows, key=lambda r: r.gross_margin_pct, reverse=True)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sensitivity Analysis"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Margin health in a static period is less actionable than understanding how margin responds to changes. Three levers dominate GenAI feature margins: LLM price changes, user volume growth, and subscription price increases."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import dataclasses\n\ndef margin_sensitivity(\n    report: FeatureMarginReport,\n    llm_price_delta: float = 0.0,    # fractional change e.g. +0.10 = +10%\n    volume_delta: float = 0.0,       # fractional change in active users\n    price_delta: float = 0.0,        # fractional change in revenue per user\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"What-if: how do margin metrics shift under given deltas?\"\"\"\"\n    base_rev = report.revenue.total_revenue_usd\n    base_llm = report.costs.llm_cost_usd\n\n    new_rev = base_rev * (1 + volume_delta) * (1 + price_delta)\n    new_llm = base_llm * (1 + volume_delta) * (1 + llm_price_delta)\n    new_infra = report.costs.infra_cost_usd * (1 + volume_delta * 0.7)  # infra scales sub-linearly\n    new_fixed = report.costs.support_alloc_usd + report.costs.rd_alloc_usd\n\n    new_gross_profit = new_rev - new_llm - new_infra\n    new_gm_pct = new_gross_profit / new_rev * 100 if new_rev else 0.0\n\n    return {\n        \"scenario\": {\"llm_price_delta\": llm_price_delta, \"volume_delta\": volume_delta, \"price_delta\": price_delta},\n        \"new_revenue_usd\": round(new_rev, 2),\n        \"new_llm_cost_usd\": round(new_llm, 2),\n        \"new_gross_margin_pct\": round(new_gm_pct, 2),\n        \"delta_gm_pct\": round(new_gm_pct - report.gross_margin_pct, 2),\n    }"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Key insight from sensitivity runs: a 20% LLM price reduction (negotiated rate or model switch) typically improves gross margin by 6\u20138 percentage points \u2014 more than a 10% subscription price increase (3\u20134pp). Optimise the cost side first."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
