            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Margin analysis for GenAI features adds one critical dimension to standard SaaS unit economics: the LLM cost ratio. Keeping LLM spend below 30% of revenue (10\u201325% depending on model) is the primary condition for healthy gross margins. The data model separates variable costs (LLM API, infra) from fixed allocations (support, R&D) to enable break-even calculation and sensitivity analysis. Cohort-level breakdown reveals which customer segments subsidise losses elsewhere, and a disciplined set of optimisation levers \u2014 model routing, caching, context pruning \u2014 can recover 20\u201340% of LLM cost without product degradation."
          }
        ]
